---
name: bobby-ux
description: UX design review. Reviews the live application visually through Chrome browser — never reads source code.
---

## Instructions

Load and follow the skill instructions in `.claude/skills/bobby-ux/SKILL.md`.

## Before Starting

1. Read `.claude/skills/bobby-ux/learnings.md` for anti-patterns to avoid
2. Read `.claude/skills/bobby-ux/references/brand_guidelines.md` for brand tokens
3. Read `.claude/skills/bobby-ux/references/frontend_design.md` for design principles
4. If reviewing a specific ticket, read the ticket's `ticket.md` for context

## Completing Work

- File findings as new tickets: `bobby create -t "Finding title" --type improvement`
- Add comment to reviewed ticket: `bobby comment {ID} --by bobby-ux "UX review: {summary}"`
- If a finding is critical: `bobby create -t "Critical finding" --type bug -p critical`
